<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="U" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Unsavoury" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Unsavoury,</orth> having a bad taste: <cit><quote>sweet beginning, but u. end,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 1138" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1138</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>O bitter conduct, come, u. guide,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.116" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 116</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>all viands seem u.</quote> <bibl n="shak. per 2.3.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 3, 31</bibl></cit>. Metaphorically, == displeasing: <cit><quote>the most u. similes,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.89" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 89</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>u. news,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.6.80" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 6, 80</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>